  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Evidence confidence is explicitly ~50% on several factors due to limited sample size and single-condition testing; this is documented honestly. Despite low confidence on some evidence items, the structured uncertainty quantification shows all QoI differences remain within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96), and the assessment team accepts the residual limitation as documented. Decision: Accepted with documented rationale grounded in quantified uncertainty.",
