    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single test condition (ASTM F1717 standard protocol: quasi-static compression-bending at 2 mm/min, ambient temperature 23±2°C, standard UHMWPE surrogate blocks). Only one loading rate and one temperature evaluated. Required level 3 calls for at least two test conditions to characterize condition sensitivity; only one condition available. Achieved level 2 (single well-characterized condition) does not meet required level 3. This shortfall is explicitly documented. Assessment team reviewed the gap: the COU is limited to the F1717 standard protocol condition, and the model is not claimed to generalize beyond this condition. The gap is accepted as a scoped limitation of the COU rather than a disqualifying deficiency, consistent with the COU description which notes this factor below required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equiv-inputs-level3",
      "rationale": "FEA model inputs mapped directly to experimentally measured specimen parameters: screw geometry from CMM measurements, material properties from lot-specific coupon testing, boundary conditions replicating test fixture geometry (fixture dimensions measured and modeled). Correspondence table prepared mapping each model input to its experimental counterpart with traceability reference. No surrogate or assumed inputs used for primary QoIs. Equivalency confirmed by independent reviewer. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level3",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed for all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) using both absolute percent difference and the validation metric E/uval per ASME V&V 10.1. Pre-established acceptance bounds: <10% QoI difference AND E/uval < 1.96. Results: stiffness 1.4%/0.61, yield force 1.5%/0.72, force at 40 mm 1.1%/0.54. All three QoIs pass both criteria. Uncertainty in experimental mean (SEM) and model prediction uncertainty (from UQ propagation) both included in E/uval denominator. Wide prediction intervals (approaching 10% bound for force at 40 mm) explicitly documented with ~50% confidence assessment. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
